##In order to be able to go to support Wuhan, the nurse's wife cancelled our wedding ceremony on earth

Micro Signal thelivings

The function introduction, reconstructs our life with the narrative beauty.

"If it happens again, you sign up and try to join the second team. I'll join the psychological support team when I'm out of quarantine. You Go, I go. They can't come. Let's go! "

Illustration by Guan Binbin

Soliciting contributions

From the first case of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan on December 8,2019, to the full outbreak on January 20,2020, the development of the situation is gripping everyone's heart.
It was a war that broke out at the beginning of the new year around every ordinary, ordinary Chinese.
This is our war, and we discuss it eagerly, analyze it carefully, deplore the loss of life in disaster, be moved by the audacity of the healer, and be Fear Is the Key by all human error, for all the little things we can do for them.
The Sea of life, let us hold hands in troubled times, and walk and cherish.
Netease's "the new pneumonia: Our War" feature tells the story of how we meet the epidemic every single day.

New Crown Pneumonia our war has been serialized 01

January 27,2020, the third day of the first lunar month.
My phone has been ringing since this morning. My in-laws, my parents, have been calling to check on me and my wife.
I dare not to be angry, to the old people back and forth to reply is the same two sentences: "We are very good, do not worry" , "you do not go out, stay at home in peace, and wait things over. "
Although I comforted the old people on the phone, my hands kept going back and forth to touch things, my heart can not be at peace.
My wife is a nurse at the intensive-care unit.

January 21,2020, the 27th of the 12th month.
My parents took a bus from their hometown in Xiaogan, Hubei Province, to the Wuhan Tianhe Airport, where they were going to fly to us to plan our wedding.
After my wife and I got our licenses, the old people on both sides set the wedding at the Twelfth Day of the first lunar month. The wife applied early for a leave of absence, but cancelled it immediately after the outbreak.
In the early morning of the 22nd, I just picked up my parents at the airport, my wife called me: "You have to buy a ticket for my parents to go back to Wuhan, go back now, don't come over! "
As soon as my parents got off the plane, my wife sent them home, and it set me on fire. I can not help but to the mobile phone roared up: "You do not see, want to go where! "
After yelling, I hung up.
A few days ago, I want to give my parents to book air tickets, Wuhan has the news of the epidemic, my wife told me: "It is not clear (virus) is not human-to-human transmission, or tell my parents not to come, and wait. "
It was hard for me to accept that both our parents were far away, that we were both medical professionals, and that it was hard to find the right time for a wedding or a vacation.
Our wedding's been dragging on. As the New Year drew near, our mother-in-law, who never hurried us, became the most anxious one, and she demanded that we both get married this year.
That day, we had a big quarrel, after the quarrel I did not listen to his wife's words, or insisted that parents come from Hubei.
Sitting in the car, my mother leaned over carefully and asked, "are you fighting again? What about... "
"It's all right. " I started the car. "Don't ask. "
Back to the neighborhood parked car, I looked up, no lights at home, do not know if his wife is at home. I hesitated and thought about what she had said before, not daring my parents to go upstairs first.
I picked up the phone and called my wife, who said she was getting ready for work.
"where are you going again? Parents are here, you do not know to come down to see? " I still have no good tone.
"Don't tell you, inform shift, manpower is not enough, I want to go now. " She hurriedly hung up the phone.
My wife's hospital has a specialist extracorporeal lung circulation team, one of the few in the city, that is not only responsible for the day to day care of critically ill patients in times of emergency, but also at any time to prevent the temporary transfer of other hospitals.
That's when I realized the epidemic might be getting worse.

January 23,2020, the 29th of the 12th month.
When I woke up in the morning, I turned on my cell phone, and all I could hear was that Wuhan had shut down the city. My parents have already prepared to go to another city to isolate themselves for 14 days, not to return home to Hubei.
I want you to stay with me for the New Year, but my dad said, "you all work at the hospital. We come from a small place, where people are small, do not move, we are wearing masks all the way, you do not worry. There's nothing physically wrong with us, but staying here is going to affect your work."
My parents stayed at my house for one night.
During that time, I called my wife's phone, which always said "out of service. ". I can't tell if she left her phone on airplane mode on purpose, or if she left it in a lab with no signal.
As I prepared to drive my parents away, I frantically clicked on the screen and kept calling my wife. My father took my phone away, "okay, she is doing this job, this time you give her trouble, is to give her trouble. "
"Are you going to get married? " I turned my head and complained loudly.
"Knot! " My mother said, "Why not? Such a good daughter-in-law, when this matter is over, give you the scenery knot! "

My wife took the night shift after I sent my parents away. She took time to send a message before the break: "The hospital to organize a medical team, in the near future may want to fly to Wuhan, I want to sign up. "
My heart suddenly like falling off a cliff, will only jump at random. I started dialing her like crazy. I called her a dozen times, but I only got through once.
"You'RE NOT GOING! " I said four words, and she hung up immediately.
His wife got off the night shift, slept briefly for a few hours in the office lounge, and got up to resume her duties. She developed hypoglycemia because she didn't have time to drink water and eat on time.
The next morning, my wife sent me a message: "unable to join the first support team for medical reasons. "
I immediately relieved, and immediately called her, "you listen to me, to tell the boss, say you have contact with my parents, high-risk groups, apply for home quarantine, do not go anywhere, okay? "
"You are a fucking white coat, this time to tell such a lie, you have no sense of responsibility? " Finish, she hung up the phone.
We had been together since Freshman Year of college, and for the first time in years, my wife had never had such a Tantrum with me. I'm afraid to call you back.
Although we are both doctors, but different professional, each other rarely ask about the work of each other.
During the period before the Spring Festival, my wife and I hardly have time to meet, often she comes home, I go out, I come back, she is not at home. We don't have time to talk. We fight over the phone.
I suddenly realized that my wife had deliberately not seen my parents for the past two days, perhaps as a precaution, as she had always feared she would not be able to hold down her post.
I understand, if there is a situation at this time, to his wife's stubborn character, she is bound to be in the first time on the line. I understood at once why she was so unkind to my parents on the subject of "stay or go. ".

All the hospitals in the city immediately issued a training notice on the new coronavirus. But until Wuhan before the closure of the city, I did not expect things would come to this point.
The whole circle of friends is buying masks and asking for all kinds of so-called "inside information" . The Internet is full of information about the epidemic, true or false, and from time to time there are some official announcements to dispel rumors. No one in the street, the community can only hear the sound of sporadic cars in the distance, I felt the panic of the atmosphere.
By the afternoon, the wife was finally able to go home. I looked at her car from the window from far and near, and finally stopped downstairs to calm down.
"husband, I want to eat a bowl of wonton. " The wife entered the house only to say a word.
I went into the kitchen and started a fire. I don't know why, but I started boiling Wonton and crying. My wife saw me do not go out for a long time, walked in, she hugged me from behind, said softly: "It's okay, it will pass. "
When my wife Ate Wonton, I once again summoned up the courage to persuade her: "Tell your leaders, do not go to work, just stay at home, when a holiday? "
My wife slowly put down her chopsticks, took a breath, staring straight at me, "at this time, we medical staff do not go, who go? Let the elderly children go? "
I can't speak.
She added: "You just stay home, do your chores, take care of my brother. When you're out of quarantine and ready to go back to work, that's where you belong. "

After College, my wife became a nurse, and I became a therapist.
We worked hard in this city together, because my wife, I also fell in love with the city, the people, the landscape, the food.
Unlike most people who choose nursing because of employment, the reason why a wife chooses to be a nurse is very simple, because she wants to do it.
When we first met, she told me: "when the doctor, I do not divide enough, then I learn nursing, also treat patients. "
On the surface, she looks nervous and confused, but in fact she is a person of great principle and perseverance. Especially in urging me to wash the dishes, mop these things, never tired, timely.
In 2014, she took an internship. Many of her classmates were looking for an internship at the local school. Only she went to Guangzhou with a few other nursing students, and it took nine months.
Thinking to be apart for so long, I have some resentment, pretending to press her, "either go to Guangzhou, or separate. ". But she said: "Guangdong's medical level than we here developed, to contact the first-class hospital, to learn something real. "
During her internship, she lived with several of her classmates in a residential building near the hospital. Every day with the tutor shift, no salary.
On New Year's Day, 2015, I went to visit her in Guangdong Province, and she insisted on cooking me a bowl of noodles to welcome me to her home.
I ate the noodles with tears in my eyes.
When she was officially employed, she insisted on going to the new intensive-care unit, which I strenuously objected to -- as if she were a 16 foot 12 inch woman who weighed 90 pounds and couldn't take care of herself? I can't imagine.
But she went anyway.
ICU, a place where you live and die every day. She used to be a little girl who hid every time she saw a dog, but she stayed there for three years. One big night shift, two small night shifts, two day shifts, it's the same cycle all the time. She also had scapulohumeral periarthritis, Neurasthenia, varicose veins, and any other occupational disease that medical care might have.
I don't know how many times, she came home tired to sleep, spread out on the bed, toss and turn. I just gave her this lame massage I learned on the Internet to relax her muscles.
Whenever this time, she would try to comfort me: "Such a good husband, to hide quietly, can not give others found. "
But I can not laugh, each time carefully asked her, "or, change a department bar. "
She'd just wave her hand and bury her head deep into the pillow.
In 2017, she had a fever and tried to get up for the night shift. I put her on the bed, dial the head nurse's phone to help her to ask for leave, did not expect the phone just connected, she snatched the phone in the past, said: "nurse, I now go to the clinic, check first, no problem I go to work. "
Before going out, she also consoled me, "the intensive-care unit was established soon, shoulder the responsibility of the hospital's critically ill patients, a radish a pit, usually are overloaded operation
She was in a speech contest at the hospital. I read her speech, there was a passage that read: "I remember vividly every night shift, the ICU corridor, only the nurses and doctors footsteps. ". We dare not stop, because we know that every step towards the direction, there is a life-and-death struggle with patients."

The day my wife and I got our marriage license, my father-in-law said something to me at the dinner table:
"Why did you send her to medical school? Because in times of trouble and The Great Leap, those who study medicine can save themselves and save the world. To be virtuous, to accumulate good fortune for future generations. It is nothing to live in poverty, with a clear conscience and a secure life. It's called a good home, and there must be a good family."
It was the first time my father-in-law and I had a serious conversation, so I remember it well. I repeated this to my wife once, and asked her, "did your father ever tell you that? "
"Hey, hey, you can hear the calluses, " she said with a laugh.
My father-in-law is a police officer with more than 30 years of police experience. He was going to retire this year.
He stayed at the police station and stayed up all night on duty like a young man. I began to understand why her career became so "axial" -- as, apparently, she was shaped by her father's example.
Later, I told my parents what my father-in-law said. My mother sighed and said, "you're in luck. Her father has raised a good daughter. "
My wife and I were born into a normal family, and our parents couldn't give us much financial support. Everything we had was hard won. I never thought we'd have a national epidemic like this when we finally have the power to have our own wedding.
In the presence of a large country and a small family, the wife chooses the former. I've been thinking a lot about how we're gonNA talk to the old people on both sides about postponing the wedding.
When my mother got the call from me, she hardly hesitated, "Anyway, Wuhan is closed, and all the planes and cars in Hubei are stopped, so we won't be able to go back for a while. Now my family supports her work, when the epidemic ends, and when you get married. Don't pressure her, just support her. She has a heavy responsibility, you must understand."
When she called her mother-in-law, she was worried: "She couldn't handle it, or she would say she wanted to get married and take a leave of absence... " but her father-in-law's voice came over before she had finished speaking, "You tell her not to worry. These are desperate times. WORK COMES FIRST! "
The mother-in-law sighed and hung up.
I no longer persuade his wife to leave the post, honestly with the unit to report the parents'movements, and told his parents to register with the current location of the neighborhood committee, do not go out, waiting for the end of isolation.
I also began to self-isolation at home, do not go out, ordered take-out also let the boy put at the door, wait for people to leave me to take. Now and Then, Here and There, on the other hand, wanted to go back to work more than usual, because my wife was fighting in the hospital, and I wanted to be with her.
I knew my wife would apply to join the team again, thinking twice, I also sent a text message to the hospital leadership:
"Director, my wife and I have no symptoms and my family have no symptoms, please rest assured. I'm a party member. I'm in charge now. If I go back to work and the outbreak gets worse, the hospital will send someone to Wuhan, even if I'm not a professional, I'm asking to be sent there, because that's my hometown. If my family needs to be examined in the meantime, we will do our best to cooperate."
When I told my wife the news, she replied with a "Kiss" face.

By the time I write this, our city has confirmed several cases of the new coronavirus in infectious disease hospitals.
The hospital where my wife is because of the transfer of a number of medical staff to assist Wuhan, manpower has become scarce, she can only work around the clock. As soon as she gets home these days, she will take a rest right after eating.
The phone she keeps by her bed is connected to a Bluetooth speaker and is turned up to full volume. She was afraid of missing the emergency call from the department. Because of her poor sleep, she takes a melatonin before going to bed. "If I can't sleep with this, I'll take a sleeping pill, " she said
This morning, the department called her, she immediately got up to get ready for work. As she went out, she sat in the doorway, tired, and hurried to put her shoes on her feet. As she stepped into her shoes, she suddenly paused. "Where are our parents? Make sure you call them and say hello. "
All of a sudden, my tears started to boil and I shook my head, unable to speak.
"Hey, hey, it's okay, " she said, touching my face. "Tell them to stay back. We'll go. "
"HMMM! " I bowed my head, tidying up her slippers, afraid to see her disappear in the elevator figure.
I remember the first time she met my parents. Without hesitation, she opened her mouth and shouted, "Hello, MOM and dad! " My mom was stunned. She didn't know what to say. My Dad's hands were twisting and his mouth was trembling. "Oh, I'm not ready to change my words
My mother's old cold legs could not adapt to the weather in the south. Last July, she came to us in the rainy season. Her legs hurt so much that she could not sleep.
My wife does moxibustion for my mother every day, and whenever she has time, she takes her for walks downstairs. My mother always told me: "If you quarrel with her again, get out yourself, I just think I raised a daughter. "
On this day, the wife's Hospital, the first group of medical team to ride to the aid of Wuhan set out, the technical backbone of the intensive-care unit to join this team. They're the only professionals here, who have the skills to perform extracorporeal circulation, a technique that can greatly improve the chances of survival in patients with severe pneumonia.
His wife took the time to send a friend circle: "Refueling Wuhan, wish the companion safe and triumphant return! " She also let me quickly click like.
I know, at this time she must also want to go to Wuhan Line, with her lovely little friends together, heal people. I immediately texted her: "If they call again, you sign up and try to join the second team. When I'm out of quarantine, I'll join the support team. You Go, I go. They can't come. Let's go! "
I kept the TV on at home, watching Hubei Satellite TV to keep an eye on the epidemic. The National Medical Team to assist Wuhan, has been in place one after another, a professional medical team from Chongqing, is urgent assembly, will soon go to work, to my home.
Friends back home are retweeting messages: where the hospital also needs what supplies, the number of donor phone.
I still can not out of the community, can only go to the garage downstairs, the electric car charged, placed in the nearest door out of the community. And at home boil a big pot of porridge, with the induction cooker small fire kept warm.
I sent a message to my wife: "If someone in the hospital needs something to eat, I'll send it to them as soon as possible. I can't get to work. At least do what I can. "
"You can drop it, your porridge who... " the phone only returned half a message, it should be no time to send. After about half an hour, she sent a kiss on the face, and then, there was no more news.
Wife's younger brother is on the junior high school, the winter vacation came to us here to play. This semester, he took an examination in the Class A penultimate ten, to my home has been playing games, do not do homework. My wife is too busy with work to take care of him these days. I take care of him all the time.
But even these last few days, my brother could sense something, and he kept asking me about the epidemic and his sister's work. In addition to doing homework, he and I stared at Hubei Satellite TV, but also from time to time with me to show him and his friends chat records, all with wuhan-related information.
In the morning when the wife went out, the younger brother did not come out, he did winter vacation homework in the room honestly. I cooked porridge into the room, patted him, and joked with him: "You are not isolated, go out to move a bit, play ball, nest at home to do? "
He bowed his head, hand did not stop, "sister came back from work, I would like to tell her homework finished, so that she does not worry. "
I noticed that there seemed to be traces of dried water on the copied paper. Maybe he's grown up a little.

At the time of writing, phone calls from both parents have been nonstop.
His father-in-law says there is now a confirmed case in his hometown, in the city where they live. I thought that the old man some panic, hurriedly told: "You do not be afraid, do not go out, just stay at home, to the market must wear a mask. "
I didn't expect my father-in-law to interrupt me, he said calmly: "Just want you to tell her, we are fine, will not go out casually, will not let relatives come over. ". Tell her not to worry about us, not to worry about grandma, to stay on the job, to take care of herself. Don't you worry about anything at home."
After a while, my mother also called, she is still worried about whether we fight: "You have to let her, she works hard, and now there is some danger, you do things at home... "
"Yes mom, we're fine. We're not going anywhere. We're staying home, " I interrupted.
"No, " my mother said. "Son, listen to me. What this country needs right now is people like you. You go where your country needs you. Your father and I don't need you to worry, don't worry about us, we're fine here, with food and shelter and play."
Put down the phone, my tears and not to do one's best to flow down.
On TV, professionals and protective materials from all over the country are hurtling toward Wuhan. There are countless medical professionals like my wife who are on the front lines. Those colleagues who work in the hospital, at this time to end the leave, stick to their posts.
My Circle of friends retweeted a picture that read: they're all kids, but they put on white coats and become death defying warriors.
Are they children? I dare not say. They have wives, husbands, children and parents. They are just ordinary people. But are they warriors? Yes! They were in white coats, fighting on the front lines of the epidemic, putting up a wall of flesh in front of everyone.
As his wife said, "don't come. We'll go where we are needed. "

After College, my wife became a nurse, and I became a therapist.
We worked hard in this city together, because my wife, I also fell in love with the city, the people, the landscape, the food.
Unlike most people who choose nursing because of employment, the reason why a wife chooses to be a nurse is very simple, because she wants to do it.
When we first met, she told me: "when the doctor, I do not divide enough, then I learn nursing, also treat patients. "
On the surface, she looks nervous and confused, but in fact she is a person of great principle and perseverance. Especially in urging me to wash the dishes, mop these things, never tired, timely.
In 2014, she took an internship. Many of her classmates were looking for an internship at the local school. Only she went to Guangzhou with a few other nursing students, and it took nine months.
Thinking to be apart for so long, I have some resentment, pretending to press her, "either go to Guangzhou, or separate. ". But she said: "Guangdong's medical level than we here developed, to contact the first-class hospital, to learn something real. "
During her internship, she lived with several of her classmates in a residential building near the hospital. Every day with the tutor shift, no salary.
On New Year's Day, 2015, I went to visit her in Guangdong Province, and she insisted on cooking me a bowl of noodles to welcome me to her home.
I ate the noodles with tears in my eyes.
When she was officially employed, she insisted on going to the new intensive-care unit, which I strenuously objected to -- as if she were a 16 foot 12 inch woman who weighed 90 pounds and couldn't take care of herself? I can't imagine.
But she went anyway.
ICU, a place where you live and die every day. She used to be a little girl who hid every time she saw a dog, but she stayed there for three years. One big night shift, two small night shifts, two day shifts, it's the same cycle all the time. She also had scapulohumeral periarthritis, Neurasthenia, varicose veins, and any other occupational disease that medical care might have.
I don't know how many times, she came home tired to sleep, spread out on the bed, toss and turn. I just gave her this lame massage I learned on the Internet to relax her muscles.
Whenever this time, she would try to comfort me: "Such a good husband, to hide quietly, can not give others found. "
But I can not laugh, each time carefully asked her, "or, change a department bar. "
She'd just wave her hand and bury her head deep into the pillow.
In 2017, she had a fever and tried to get up for the night shift. I put her on the bed, dial the head nurse's phone to help her to ask for leave, did not expect the phone just connected, she snatched the phone in the past, said: "nurse, I now go to the clinic, check first, no problem I go to work. "
Before going out, she also consoled me, "the intensive-care unit was established soon, shoulder the responsibility of the hospital's critically ill patients, a radish a pit, usually are overloaded operation
She was in a speech contest at the hospital. I read her speech, there was a passage that read: "I remember vividly every night shift, the ICU corridor, only the nurses and doctors footsteps. ". We dare not stop, because we know that every step towards the direction, there is a life-and-death struggle with patients."

In addition to doing homework, he and I stared at Hubei Satellite TV, but also from time to time with me to show him and his friends chat records, all with wuhan-related information.

In the morning when the wife went out, the younger brother did not come out, he did winter vacation homework in the room honestly. I cooked porridge into the room, patted him, and joked with him: "You are not isolated, go out to move a bit, play ball, nest at home to do? "

He bowed his head, hand did not stop, "sister came back from work, I would like to tell her homework finished, so that she does not worry. "

I noticed that there seemed to be traces of dried water on the copied paper. Maybe he's grown up a little.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the time of writing, phone calls from both parents have been nonstop.
His father-in-law says there is now a confirmed case in his hometown, in the city where they live. I thought that the old man some panic, hurriedly told: "You do not be afraid, do not go out, just stay at home, to the market must wear a mask. "
I didn't expect my father-in-law to interrupt me, he said calmly: "Just want you to tell her, we are fine, will not go out casually, will not let relatives come over. ". Tell her not to worry about us, not to worry about grandma, to stay on the job, to take care of herself. Don't you worry about anything at home."
After a while, my mother also called, she is still worried about whether we fight: "You have to let her, she works hard, and now there is some danger, you do things at home... "
"Yes mom, we're fine. We're not going anywhere. We're staying home, " I interrupted.
"No, " my mother said. "Son, listen to me. What this country needs right now is people like you. You go where your country needs you. Your father and I don't need you to worry, don't worry about us, we're fine here, with food and shelter and play."
Put down the phone, my tears and not to do one's best to flow down.
On TV, professionals and protective materials from all over the country are hurtling toward Wuhan. There are countless medical professionals like my wife who are on the front lines. Those colleagues who work in the hospital, at this time to end the leave, stick to their posts.
My Circle of friends retweeted a picture that read: they're all kids, but they put on white coats and become death defying warriors.
Are they children? I dare not say. They have wives, husbands, children and parents. They are just ordinary people. But are they warriors? Yes! They were in white coats, fighting on the front lines of the epidemic, putting up a wall of flesh in front of everyone.
As his wife said, "don't come. We'll go where we are needed. "
